Summary:
The new year rings in with a few new hardware developments with new machines rumored or leaked in advance of CES. There’s Chrome software news too though: You can run the bleeding edge Canary version of Chrome OS. Should you?
The new year starts off with a new Chrome Show and this week there’s much discussion on new hardware in the works from Samsung, LG and Toshiba. A clever method will let you run the Canary channel of Chrome OS but it’s not for the faint of heart — or a Chromebook that’s a primary device. And our extension of the week is perfect for any new year’s resolutions of being more productive.
